Great family owned and run facility, strong Alpharetta ties. Bagels made in house along with other pastries and sandwiches. 2 locations in Alpharetta and a new one in sandy springs. Try it you'll like it. Ask for John the owner, tell him jim sent you!
Nice, fluffy bagels. Toppings and flavors are great. They are very involved in the community, support local businesses who support you!

Missing item on Uber eats order. I Called the store to question the item I paid for and did not receive. I choose to call bagal boys as their staff packs and makes the food. The cashier and the manager refused to accept responsibility for the missing item. Management claims the Uber driver packs all food items that go out for delivery, and  therefore is solely accountable for any missing products. The only solution offered was for me to drive to them and pick up the item, with no offer to refund me in any way.  Their error was forgivable, the handling of the error was not. The missing item ruin our business breakfast meeting. I will NEVER use this eatery again. Extremely poor business

Great atmosphere and yummy bagels! Their bagels are light and the ones I have tried are delicious! They have lots of different flavors and different flavored cream cheese too! I have not tried the other food on the huge menu but there are a lot of choices!

I'm from NYC and these are as close to a real bagel I've had in GA, however several times I get there before noon and they're out of a certain popular bagel and not making more.  They're open until 2, can you throw in another batch of poppy seeds in the oven at 11:30am, I'm sure they'll sell :-) .

The place is nice if you like bagel sandwiche. I wish they had vegan options because the sandwiches smell really good. The cold rush smoothie is good and very sweet. My coworker stated the cinnamon bagel tasted like a regular bagel with cinnamon sprinkled on top not really baked in.  Staff is friendly and patient. Bathroom was clean. They encouraged 6ft apart seating.

Great customer service. I had a coupon for a free bagel and cream cheese. The manager walked me through the menu and I ordered the cheddar cheese bagel, delicious!

Bagel Boys is a great place to order breakfast from during this crazy time of Covid19. They have a large variety of fresh bagels.  The spinach , bacon , egg and artichoke bagel remains our favorite. The orange juice is delicious.

Unfortunately, we were disappointed with our visit today, we ordered a breakfast bowl, a sandwich bagel and an Asiago bagel with cream cheese. The breakfast bowl was like microwaved eggs, a cut up tomato and sausage, there was water in the bottom of the bowl....there was no fruit that we ordered and they said we are out of fruit and just gave you a hash brown they cost the same. The bagel wasn't toasted and there was no cream cheese that we paid for, so we asked. This place was busy and has received good reviews so hopefully they were just off today.

Don't let the nice photos on the website foul you. If you look at the photos on the website it looks like a really nice lush beautiful location but it's not. It's in a rundown shopping center and it doesn't look as clean as a could be. I placed an order for a lox and bagel and I will tell you that I'm extremely disappointed. I guess maybe I've been spoiled by going to Goldberg's deli but I will tell you that this sandwich was absolutely not worth the price I paid. There was hardly any cream cheese on it and the cream cheese that was on it didn't even taste like cream cheese. The lox that was on my bagel didn't even taste like I was cured but more like a fresh salmon and I was extremely disappointed. This would not be a place I would go to ever again.
Good NYC-style bagels, quite authentic. This is my second favorite spot for bagels in Alpharetta/Milton area. Good and quick service too.

Bagel Boys is always great. The service is always friendly, the bagels are tasty and they refill the bagel bins as fast as they are emptied. I pass closer bagel joints just to go there. If you want a bagel, or a baker's dozen, they're worth checking out.

We didn't know Bagel Boys was right around the corner from us. We decided to use them for a church group breakfast and it was a total hit. I walked in on a Saturday to place my order, met the owner, and found him to be attentive and totally focused on customer service. He took the order, gave me a contact person in case he wasn't there, and the food was ready on time. I haven't even started on the taste and selection--wow! Fresh, warm bagels with a huge variety of recipes, well-presented in the case, and fast friendly staff. You can tell when service starts from the top-down, and this place is a good example. We've been back since!
Great stop

This place doesn't just offer amazing breakfast but also serves up phenomenal lunches. They offer delicious bagels, sandwiches and even soups and salads. Everything is made fresh and is top-notch. Plus service is friendly and speedy. They also offer free WiFi in case you want to sit around and get some work done. So many options too.

Maybe it's because we were there the day after Irma, but food wasn't good. Roast beef sandwich had green sheen. Fruit cup had white fuzz-asked for a replacement, no fuzz but fruit was mush. Egg white sandwich was good. Mini muffin tasted day old. Orange juice was good. Fountain drinks good. I had the medium roast Kona coffee- good but not hot. Bathroom unkept. Made me wish I had gone straight to the Starbucks next door.

Love the employees there, one afternoon at 2:30 pm on a Sat, they had already closed but she made me a smoothie anyway. I do go into store about 3 times a week, but she didnt have to make for me and she did anyway and I was really craving a strawberry smoothie  and am very thankful for her going up and above...that my dear is how you keep folks happy for slackers like me and not realizing the time.  Wanted the world to know that is great customer service every time I go, but today was super. Thanks guys for doing all you do.

one of the few places I will get up early for.  They have great bagels, but they are even better when still warm.  The owners are friendly and there is obviously a serious focus on customer service.  They cost a little bit more, but well worth the cost.

UPDATE! I owe Bagel Boy Cafe a huge apology. I accidentally posted my bad review to their site & I am very sorry. The place I had the bad experience with is Brooklyn Bagel Bakery, NOT Bagel Boy Cafe. I have never visited Bagel Boy Cafe, but will do so very soon. Again, please accept my apology for an incorrectly placed negative review.  The below review is in reference to a recent visit to Brooklyn Bagel Bakery, not Bagel Boy Cafe!  "Their bagels are good. But, let me describe their ruben. You need a microscope to find the meat. They are so cheap, that they served a sliver of a pickle, and their coleslaw was dry. Yes, dry coleslaw. Can you believe it?"
I hate cream cheese but theirs is the only one I'll eat, kind of expensive food but by far the best bagels I've ever had.

Waited 25 min for 2 bagels and still didn't get what I asked for. Good idea to staff 1 person to make bagels on Labor Day - who knew with everyone off, that people would go out for breakfast?! I give the manager/owner an F for being incompetent - I suggest visiting Einsteins and taking lessons.
